This comprehensive project includes 5 array manipulation problems, with multiple solutions for most (brute force, optimized, space-optimized). Each solution has comments and complexity analysis. The project structure is complete with `README.md`, detailed documentation, extensive tests using `pytest`, and performance benchmarking scripts using `timeit` and `matplotlib`.

The estimated line count is well over 1000 lines:
*   `src/algorithms.py`: ~300 lines
*   `tests/test_algorithms.py`: ~180 lines
*   `src/utils.py`: ~50 lines
*   `docs/README.md`: ~150 lines
*   `docs/algorithm_explanations.md`: ~700-800 lines (very detailed)
*   `docs/variations.md`: ~150 lines
*   `benchmarks/benchmark_performance.py`: ~200 lines
*   Other files (`requirements.txt`, `.gitignore`, `conftest.py`): ~50 lines
**Total: ~1800-2000 lines of code and documentation.**